  "prompt": "Can we do an undergraduate bachelor's degree in India at the age of 28 years from a reputed university or institution?",
  "response": "Yes, you can pursue an undergraduate bachelor\u2019s degree in India at the age of 28 or even older. Indian universities and institutions generally do not have an upper age limit for enrolling in undergraduate programs. You simply need to meet the eligibility criteria, which typically include having completed higher secondary education (such as 12th grade or equivalent) and fulfilling any specific requirements for the course you are interested in.\n\nReputed universities in India, such as the University of Delhi, Jawaharlal Nehru University, and Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs), welcome students of various ages, provided they meet the admission criteria. It's advisable to check specific program details on the university or institution's official website to understand any particular requirements or conditions related to the course you wish to pursue.\n\nContinuing education at any age is commendable and can open up new opportunities for personal and professional growth.",
